  "x-jpcm-normative-rules": [
    "All side-effecting messages MUST include at least one valid CapabilityLease reference and MUST be rechecked by the adapter immediately before effect execution.",
    "R4, R5, and R6 messages MUST be D4-authority-serialized unless a policy decision explicitly permits lower delivery class.",
    "Voice-originated intents MUST pass through voice.segment.created and voice.intent.candidate before becoming work_order.created, and R2+ voice commands require readback or equivalent explicit confirmation.",
    "Self-improvement targeting policy, schema, scheduler, router, sandbox, or authority-kernel MUST require quorum and canary or shadow evaluation before deployment.",
    "No memory object may be accepted without evidence_refs and rollback_ref unless scope is temporary.",
    "No tool may be used by JMCP until a ToolManifest, audit result, sandbox profile, and conformance claim are recorded.",
    "Payload hashes are computed over canonical JSON using RFC 8785 JCS unless an approved schema profile specifies otherwise.",
    "Extensions MUST NOT override or reinterpret required fields. Services that require semantic changes MUST publish a new schema version."
  ]
